INSERT INTO `wp_options` VALUES("429", "_transient_ksd_notifications_feed", "<?xml version=\"1.0\" encoding=\"UTF-8\"?><rss version=\"2.0\"\n	xmlns:content=\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/content/\"\n	xmlns:wfw=\"http://wellformedweb.org/CommentAPI/\"\n	xmlns:dc=\"http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/\"\n	xmlns:atom=\"http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom\"\n	xmlns:sy=\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/syndication/\"\n	xmlns:slash=\"http://purl.org/rss/1.0/modules/slash/\"\n	>\n\n<channel>\n	<title>Kanzu Code &#187; Blog</title>\n	<atom:link href=\"http://kanzucode.com/work/blog/feed/\" rel=\"self\" type=\"application/rss+xml\" />\n	<link>https://kanzucode.com</link>\n	<description>Power Up</description>\n	<lastBuildDate>Tue, 30 Jun 2015 04:47:47 +0000</lastBuildDate>\n	<language>en-US</language>\n	<sy:updatePeriod>hourly</sy:updatePeriod>\n	<sy:updateFrequency>1</sy:updateFrequency>\n	<generator>http://wordpress.org/?v=4.2.2</generator>\n	<item>\n		<title>Londa Media Advisory</title>\n		<link>https://kanzucode.com/blog/londa-media-advisory/</link>\n		<comments>https://kanzucode.com/blog/londa-media-advisory/#comments</comments>\n		<pubDate>Sat, 06 Jun 2015 22:01:01 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Kakoma]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Blog]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Londa]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">https://kanzucode.com/?p=402</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>About Kanzu Code Here at Kanzu Code, we are solely focused on the creation of digital products with a clear focus on clean, functional design, simplicity and great user experience. We were born out of a need to locally build software that addresses local challenges but pushes the envelope globally. We build &#38; maintain mobile [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://kanzucode.com/blog/londa-media-advisory/\">Londa Media Advisory</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://kanzucode.com\">Kanzu Code</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<h2>About Kanzu Code</h2>\n<p>Here at Kanzu Code, we are solely focused on the creation of digital products with a clear focus on clean, functional design, simplicity and great user experience. We were born out of a need to locally build software that addresses local challenges but pushes the envelope globally. We build &amp; maintain mobile applications, websites and custom digital solutions to every day challenges. One such (huge) challenge we are currently taking on is youth apathy to politics in general and the electoral process in particular.</p>\n<h2>The Problem</h2>\n<p>A number of issues worldwide can be traced to gaps in leadership. Africa knows this only too well (and has quite a bit to show for it). This isn’t helped by the fact that the youth, who make up a large part of the population, are increasingly choosing not to take part in the electoral process, with voter turnout numbers dwindling.</p>\n<p><strong>Uganda Presidential Elections<sup>1</sup></strong></p>\n<table>\n<tbody>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"79\"><strong>Year</strong></td>\n<td width=\"106\"><strong>Voter Turn­out</strong></td>\n<td width=\"78\"><strong>Total vote</strong></td>\n<td width=\"90\"><strong>Registration</strong></td>\n<td width=\"108\"><strong>Voting age population</strong></td>\n<td width=\"108\"><strong>Population</strong></td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"79\">1996</td>\n<td width=\"106\">72.‌60%</td>\n<td width=\"78\">6,163,678</td>\n<td width=\"90\">8,489,915</td>\n<td width=\"108\">9,875,250</td>\n<td width=\"108\">21,945,000</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"79\">2001</td>\n<td width=\"106\">70.‌31%</td>\n<td width=\"78\">7,576,144</td>\n<td width=\"90\">10,775,836</td>\n<td width=\"108\">10,206,461</td>\n<td width=\"108\">22,070,329</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"79\">2006</td>\n<td width=\"106\">69.‌19%</td>\n<td width=\"78\">7,230,456</td>\n<td width=\"90\">10,450,788</td>\n<td width=\"108\">11,820,000</td>\n<td width=\"108\">27,269,482</td>\n</tr>\n<tr>\n<td width=\"79\">2011</td>\n<td width=\"106\">59.‌29%</td>\n<td width=\"78\">8,272,760</td>\n<td width=\"90\">13,954,129</td>\n<td width=\"108\">14,954,435</td>\n<td width=\"108\">34,612,250</td>\n</tr>\n</tbody>\n</table>\n<p>The trend is worrying; over the years, more and more youth are opting not to vote. In as much as our vote may not necessarily bring the change we seek, it is one major step in the right direction.</p>\n<h2>Londa</h2>\n<p>Londa app is one part of the solution to this challenge. Built not to be a silver-bullet, Londa is stepping in to address some of the multiple reasons why we the youth aren’t voting. The app will run both as a web and mobile application that addresses some key youth concerns surrounding elections. Envisioned to be simple, fun to use but still informative, building and roll-out of the app is broken down into the following phases:</p>\n<p><strong>Phase 1: Survey</strong></p>\n<p>At least 1,000 youth are being surveyed to find out whether they intend to take part in the upcoming Uganda Presidential elections and what their reasons are for their decision. This information will guide the direction the app will take. Contacts of those interested in following the app’s journey are being collected too.</p>\n<p><strong>Phase 2: App design</strong></p>\n<p>Based on the survey results, the initial app is designed to address key needs that can be met digitally.</p>\n<p><strong>Phase 3: Development</strong></p>\n<p>A community of developers come together to build the app both on mobile and the web.</p>\n<p><strong>Phase 4: Alpha release</strong></p>\n<p>An early release of the app (Londa-alpha) is broadcast to the contact list for initial tests</p>\n<p><strong>Phase 5: Beta release</strong></p>\n<p>Based on feedback, Londa-beta is created and similarly broadcast.</p>\n<p><strong>Phase 6: Launch</strong></p>\n<p>Based on feedback to the beta version, Londa 1.0.0 is released on mobile and on the web.</p>\n<h2>More on Londa</h2>\n<p><strong>Open Source:</strong> Londa will be built to be freely re-used by developers in other countries, African or otherwise. We believe that many of the problems identified in the survey will be fairly representative of youth electoral apathy across the continent enough for the solution to be re-used.</p>\n<p><strong>Non-partisan:</strong> The app isn’t built to appeal to any party, local or otherwise. The goal is to provide a platform that addresses youth’s pain points and removes any barriers to voting.</p>\n<p><strong>Self-funded:</strong> In a bid to be as impartial as possible, the app-building process is entirely funded by Kanzu Code.</p>\n<h2>Get Involved</h2>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">To get app progress updates, test the app &amp; be a part of deciding its direction or as a developer, to be a part of the coding, join us here:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\"><div id=\"londa-newsletter\">    \n<!-- Begin MailChimp Signup Form -->\n<link href=\"//cdn-images.mailchimp.com/embedcode/classic-081711.css\" rel=\"stylesheet\" type=\"text/css\">\n<style type=\"text/css\">\n	#mc_embed_signup{background:#fff; clear:left; font:14px Helvetica,Arial,sans-serif; }\n	/* Add your own MailChimp form style overrides in your site stylesheet or in this style block.\n	   We recommend moving this block and the preceding CSS link to the HEAD of your HTML file. */\n</style>\n<div id=\"mc_embed_signup\">\n<form action=\"//kanzucode.us6.list-manage.com/subscribe/post?u=072b3e28db&amp;id=75e8251ee7\" method=\"post\" id=\"mc-embedded-subscribe-form\" name=\"mc-embedded-subscribe-form\" class=\"validate\" target=\"_blank\" novalidate>\n    <div id=\"mc_embed_signup_scroll\">\n	\n<div class=\"indicates-required\"><span class=\"asterisk\">*</span> indicates required</div>\n<div class=\"mc-field-group\">\n	<label for=\"mce-EMAIL\">Email Address  <span class=\"asterisk\">*</span>\n</label>\n	<input type=\"email\" value=\"\" name=\"EMAIL\" class=\"required email\" id=\"mce-EMAIL\">\n</div>\n<d