nd mc_embed_signup-->\n</div></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify;\">We are currently at the survey phase. Take part in the Londa survey here: <a href=\"http://surveymonkey.com/s/londa256\" target=\"_blank\">Londa Survey</a></p>\n<h2> References</h2>\n<p>1 International Institute for Democracy and Electoral Assistance (IDEA). (2011, October 5). <em>Voter turnout data for Uganda</em>. Retrieved from <a href=\"http://www.idea.int/vt/countryview.cfm?CountryCode=UG\">http://www.idea.int/vt/countryview.cfm?CountryCode=UG</a></p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://kanzucode.com/blog/londa-media-advisory/\">Londa Media Advisory</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://kanzucode.com\">Kanzu Code</a>.</p>\n]]></content:encoded>\n			<wfw:commentRss>https://kanzucode.com/blog/londa-media-advisory/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n		<slash:comments>1</slash:comments>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Thank you. Giving back</title>\n		<link>https://kanzucode.com/blog/thank-you-giving-back/</link>\n		<comments>https://kanzucode.com/blog/thank-you-giving-back/#comments</comments>\n		<pubDate>Wed, 25 Feb 2015 19:29:14 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Kakoma]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Blog]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Kanzu Support Desk]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[WordPress]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://blog.kanzucode.com/?p=26</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>We have three buddies to thank profusely today. The first is you, who&#8217;s subscribed to our blog. In as much as we truly enjoy documenting Kanzu Code&#8217;s start-up journey and Kanzu Support Desk&#8217;s hits and misses, we&#8217;d honestly not enjoy it as much if we didn&#8217;t know that you were reading. You are so committed [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://kanzucode.com/blog/thank-you-giving-back/\">Thank you. Giving back</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://kanzucode.com\">Kanzu Code</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style=\"text-align: justify\">We have three buddies to thank profusely today. The first is you, who&#8217;s subscribed to our blog. In as much as we truly enjoy documenting <a href=\"http://kanzucode.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Kanzu Code&#8217;s</a> start-up journey and <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/kanzu-support-desk/\" target=\"_blank\">Kanzu Support Desk&#8217;s</a> hits and misses, we&#8217;d honestly not enjoy it as much if we didn&#8217;t know that you were reading. You are so committed to reading, you&#8217;ve signed-up for our newsletter! Thanks!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">We&#8217;d also like to thank you who&#8217;s allowed us to track your Kanzu Support Desk (KSD) usage.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><img class=\" size-full wp-image-29 aligncenter\" src=\"http://blog.kanzucode.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/02/ksd_allow_tracking.png\" alt=\"ksd_allow_tracking\" width=\"266\" height=\"38\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">One click on your part, one huge step for humanity. True story. That benevolent move on your part has allowed us to get a better idea of how you are using KSD. We don&#8217;t track ANY personal information; we merely use Google Analytics to help us get a better picture of which features are useful to you and which ones aren&#8217;t. That click right there is helping us make KSD better for you and hundreds of other users. You are a hero.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Finally, we&#8217;d like to thank you who&#8217;s sent us feedback. So far, six features have been informed by your feedback, you awesome person you. Thank you.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">To show how grateful we are, we are giving each of you a discount on our <a href=\"https://kanzucode.com/add-ons/kanzu-support-desk-email/\" target=\"_blank\">KSD mail add-on</a>. For you who signed-up for our newsletter &amp; you who sent us feedback, you&#8217;ve already received instructions on how to access your discount and you should already be in support nirvana by now. For you who allowed us to track your usage, please update your KSD to <em><strong>version 1.5.3</strong></em> and follow the instructions.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">If you aren&#8217;t one of our bosom buddies yet, join the crew by subscribing to our blog from your KSD installation (under the &#8216;<em>Help</em>&#8216; tab) or by allowing anonymous tracking (under the &#8216;<em>settings&#8217;</em> tab). We only have <span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"><strong>99 discounts</strong></span> on our hands so quick clicks will take the day.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">*cue happy song*</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Thanks a lot for your support (<em>pun intended</em>). Enjoy your powered-up KSD experience</p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://kanzucode.com/blog/thank-you-giving-back/\">Thank you. Giving back</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://kanzucode.com\">Kanzu Code</a>.</p>\n]]></content:encoded>\n			<wfw:commentRss>https://kanzucode.com/blog/thank-you-giving-back/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Google reCAPTCHA baby</title>\n		<link>https://kanzucode.com/blog/google-recaptcha-baby/</link>\n		<comments>https://kanzucode.com/blog/google-recaptcha-baby/#comments</comments>\n		<pubDate>Thu, 05 Feb 2015 12:33:07 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Kakoma]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Blog]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Kanzu Support Desk]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[WordPress]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://blog.kanzucode.com/?p=16</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>We received this feedback from one of our users: We had addition of spam CAPTCHA to the plugin on our feature roadmap (plus 28 other features. The list won&#8217;t give a developer a break!) but it wasn&#8217;t anywhere near the top of the list. At his request (you can&#8217;t tell from the screenshot, but its [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://kanzucode.com/blog/google-recaptcha-baby/\">Google reCAPTCHA baby</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://kanzucode.com\">Kanzu Code</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style=\"text-align: justify\">We received this feedback from one of our users:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-18\" src=\"http://blog.kanzucode.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/02/kanzu_support_desk_feedback.jpeg\" alt=\"Kanzu Support Desk Feedback\" width=\"750\" height=\"309\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">We had addition of spam CAPTCHA to the plugin on our feature roadmap (plus 28 other features. The list won&#8217;t give a developer a break!) but it wasn&#8217;t anywhere near the top of the list. At his request (you can&#8217;t tell from the screenshot, but its a &#8216;he&#8217;), we moved the issue up the queue and worked on that instead. In a few hours, Google reCAPTCHA was integrated and <em><strong>KSD</strong></em> <em><strong>version 1.3.1</strong></em> was released.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">We are deliberate about using Google products; you might (or might not) have noticed that our KSD dashboard charts are done using Google Charts. Deciding to use Google reCAPTCHA to add CAPTCHA to our forms was an easy choice. We&#8217;ve added information on how to add reCAPTCHA to your support form to our <a href=\"https://kanzucode.com/documentation/wordpress-customer-service-plugin-ksd-getting-started/\" target=\"_blank\">documentation. Check it out</a> (if you haven&#8217;t already).</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><em><strong>Update February 16th, 2014:</strong></em></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">We received this feedback from one of our users:</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-38\" src=\"http://blog.kanzucode.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2015/02/ksd_recaptcha_feedback.png\" alt=\"ksd_recaptcha_feedback\" width=\"761\" height=\"112\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"> The Google reCAPTCHA validation was being done at the server side which meant that users would submit the form, then on processing, get a success or error depending on whether they&#8217;d properly checked the Google reCAPTCHA field. From this feedback, we realized that this might be a bit confusing for some. We updated to <em><strong>version 1.4.0</strong></em> to use client-side validation instead. This meant that users wouldn&#8217;t be able to submit a form before checking the Google reCAPTCHA field. This meant a much better user experience.</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://kanzucode.com/blog/google-recaptcha-baby/\">Google reCAPTCHA baby</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://kanzucode.com\">Kanzu Code</a>.</p>\n]]></content:encoded>\n			<wfw:commentRss>https://kanzucode.com/blog/google-recaptcha-baby/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Version 1.3.0 Out</title>\n		<link>https://kanzucode.com/blog/version-1-3-0-out/</link>\n		<comments>https://kanzucode.com/blog/version-1-3-0-out/#comments</comments>\n		<pubDate>Sat, 31 Jan 2015 12:20:37 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Kakoma]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Blog]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Kanzu Support Desk]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[WordPress]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://blog.kanzucode.com/?p=13</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>One of the best features about WordPress is shortcodes. Several Kanzu Support Desk versions later, we still didn&#8217;t have one. Sad. Very sad. Our focus though was primarily on making the admin user interface friendlier. This has changed with this version. We&#8217;ve added a shortcode ksd_support_form and updated our documentation to reflect it. *spontaneous celebrations [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://kanzucode.com/blog/version-1-3-0-out/\">Version 1.3.0 Out</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://kanzucode.com\">Kanzu Code</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style=\"text-align: justify\">One of the best features about WordPress is shortcodes. Several Kanzu Support Desk versions later, we still didn&#8217;t have one. Sad. Very sad. Our focus though was primarily on making the admin user interface friendlier. This has changed with this version. We&#8217;ve added a shortcode <strong>ksd_support_form</strong> and updated our documentation to reflect it. *spontaneous celebrations all round*</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Now, you can easily place your support form wherever you want it, any page, any post. More flexibility, more power. Thanks for being patient as we beat things into place. We know the shortcode will improve your user experience immensely so, rock away!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">*cue soft rock song, sip coffee*</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://kanzucode.com/blog/version-1-3-0-out/\">Version 1.3.0 Out</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://kanzucode.com\">Kanzu Code</a>.</p>\n]]></content:encoded>\n			<wfw:commentRss>https://kanzucode.com/blog/version-1-3-0-out/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n		</item>\n		<item>\n		<title>Kanzu Support Desk is born</title>\n		<link>https://kanzucode.com/blog/ksd-born/</link>\n		<comments>https://kanzucode.com/blog/ksd-born/#comments</comments>\n		<pubDate>Fri, 21 Nov 2014 16:50:46 +0000</pubDate>\n		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Kakoma]]></dc:creator>\n				<category><![CDATA[Blog]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[Kanzu Support Desk]]></category>\n		<category><![CDATA[WordPress]]></category>\n\n		<guid isPermaLink=\"false\">http://blog.kanzucode.com/?p=1</guid>\n		<description><![CDATA[<p>I was approached by a friend of mine, a developer, in July 2014 to build a customer service portal for someone. I did a number of searches to get a picture of what I was in for; what did the interwebs have to offer in terms of ticketing solutions? Info in hand, I set off [&#8230;]</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://kanzucode.com/blog/ksd-born/\">Kanzu Support Desk is born</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://kanzucode.com\">Kanzu Code</a>.</p>\n]]></description>\n				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<p style=\"text-align: justify\">I was approached by a friend of mine, a developer, in July 2014 to build a customer service portal for someone. I did a number of searches to get a picture of what I was in for; what did the interwebs have to offer in terms of ticketing solutions? Info in hand, I set off to meet my friend and the someone.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">We discussed the project and agreed that I send a formal price quotation. I did that a few days later and the trail went cold. Developers can relate with ladies in this area &#8211; you meet prospect, have coffee, send a quotation (or text, ladies, help me out here) and the prospect goes silent. I did what any developer in my situation would  have done &#8211; built the solution anyway.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">See, during the search I realized that WordPress didn&#8217;t have any native, solid customer service plugin. And I love WordPress. I got in touch with one of the most versatile developers I know, <a href=\"https://ug.linkedin.com/pub/emmanuel-ssebaggala/17/231/b12\" target=\"_blank\">Ssegga</a>, pitched the idea and we started work. I thought it&#8217;d take about 2 weeks to build&#8230;.ha, lies. Lies, I tell you! It took us close to four months. Four. Months. In that time, an average fly somewhere has spanned 4 generations. There we were, coding, for 4 fly generations.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">On <strong>21st November,2014</strong> though, finally, <a href=\"http://wordpress.org/plugins/kanzu-support-desk/\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>Kanzu Support Desk</strong></a> was made public in the WordPress plugin repository. The WordPress plugin review team took about an hour to evaluate us and let us in. I think they could immediately tell we meant business; as a precaution, we&#8217;d stationed muscular guys at their offices to convince them about how serious we were. It didn&#8217;t get to that though. We figured that since they didn&#8217;t do any real work, the muscular guys would refund our money. None of us though could find the nerve to go ask for a refund.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">We were in though; that&#8217;s all that mattered. The journey started.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><img class=\"alignnone size-full wp-image-40\" src=\"http://blog.kanzucode.com/wp-content/uploads/sites/2/2014/11/ksd_launch.png\" alt=\"ksd_launch\" width=\"600\" height=\"400\" /></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">*cue battle music*</p>\n<p>The post <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://kanzucode.com/blog/ksd-born/\">Kanzu Support Desk is born</a> appeared first on <a rel=\"nofollow\" href=\"https://kanzucode.com\">Kanzu Code</a>.</p>\n]]></content:encoded>\n			<wfw:commentRss>https://kanzucode.com/blog/ksd-born/feed/</wfw:commentRss>\n		<slash:comments>0</slash:comments>\n		</item>\n	</channel>\n</rss>\n\r\n<!-- Performance optimized by W3 Total Cache. Learn more: http://www.w3-edge.com/wordpress-plugins/\r\n\r\nPage Caching using disk: enhanced\r\n\r\n Served from: kanzucode.com @ 2015-07-21 17:07:55 by W3 Total Cache -->", "no");
